00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:38,800
 So something that is good, and we need to see it

265
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,160
 from God's sight.

266
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:44,240
 Verse two, it says, "It is like precious olive oil

267
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:48,520
 poured on the head, running down on the beer,

268
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:51,120
 running down on Aaron's beer,

269
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:53,480
 down upon his collar to his robes."

270
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,280
 You know, verse two.

271
00:15:56,240 --> 00:16:00,160
 (speaking in foreign language)

272
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:08,560
 This imagery may not sound appealing to us

273
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:10,440
 as modern people, all right?

274
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:13,200
 It sounds messy, it looks messy,

275
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,880
 but you know, you can see, you know,

276
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:18,760
 the oil pouring down on Aaron, you know,

277
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:21,360
 is in abundance, right?

278
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:24,520
 So you need to ask the question,

279
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:27,400
 as you look at verse two, every community,

280
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:32,320
 every group of people has some representatives,

281
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:34,520
 some representative leaders.

282
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:38,880
 Sometimes it is a famous person you grew up,

283
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:42,960
 you know, admitting someone, even you don't know her

284
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,400
 or you don't know him, but you know,

285
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:47,320
 you feel like, oh, they represent you.

286
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:50,520
 Maybe an artist, maybe a cultural icon.

287
00:16:50,520 --> 00:16:53,520
 If they do well and I do well, right?

288
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:56,000
 And kind of like last night,

289
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:59,400
 did you see the football game last night?

290
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:02,000
 Yeah, right?

291
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,880
 Right, did you see it?

292
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:05,760
 It's very good to see it, right?

293
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:09,640
 It's the dramatic turnaround for Bears.

294
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:12,920
 And you know, I see today when I show up at church,

295
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,040
 I see people are happy.

296
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:18,240
 We haven't felt happy for a long time, right?

297
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,600
 Chicago people.

298
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:22,280
 Anyways, so we have our own representatives.

299
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:25,800
 And you know, in the Old Testament, in Israel,

300
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:29,200
 the representative figure was the high priest Aaron.

301
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:34,320
 (speaking in foreign language)

302
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:53,480
 So when you trace the story of the Bible

303
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,760
 from the Old Testament,

304
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:57,600
 when the people of Israel came out of Egypt,

305
00:17:57,600 --> 00:18:02,600
 they arrived at Mount Sinai and they received the law

306
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:05,520
 and then the tabernacle was first established

307
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:09,480
 in the wilderness because God wanted to dwell within them.

308
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:14,040
 And Moses anointed the tabernacle and his furniture

309
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:16,080
 and all the items and set up.

310
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:20,200
 And the climax comes to anointing the high priest Aaron

311
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:24,080
 so that he can represent the whole people of God Israel

312
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:26,120
 to serve God together.

313
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:28,680
 So in the book of Leviticus, it says,

314
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:33,680
 Moses was pouring anointing olive oil on the head of Aaron

315
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:37,480
 and to anoint him to consecrate him.

316
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:41,400
 (speaking in foreign language)

317
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:46,400
 And that was the most sacred moment of the entire Bible.

318
00:18:46,400 --> 00:19:04,160
 And even says that, you know, the glory of God, you know,

319
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:12,760
 shines from the tabernacle and consume the offering

320
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:15,760
 on the altar and the people shout out loud

321
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:19,040
 and fell on their faces and they worship God together.

322
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:22,040
 That was the sacred moment of the Old Testament.

323
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:26,880
 (speaking in foreign language)

324
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:31,880
, and you can imagine that was a sacred,

325
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:51,440
 the most precious moment of all time in the Bible.

326
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:54,520
 But Psalm 133 turns it around a little bit.

327
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:57,000
 It says the kind of holiness, sacredness

328
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:01,560
 is actually present when the people of God are united.

329
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:04,240
 When they go up together to Jerusalem

330
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:07,040
 to worship God together, it's the togetherness

331
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,120
 that is sacred.

332
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:11,760
 It's just like, it is kind of like the first anointing

333
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:13,200
 of the high priest Aaron,

334
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:15,760
 when the glory of God finally comes.

335
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:18,840
 You know, it comes not because someone's being anointed.

336
00:20:18,840 --> 00:20:23,040
 It comes, the glory of God shines for

337
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:25,040
 when the people of God are united

338
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,600
 and worshiping God together.

339
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:30,600
 (speaking in foreign language)

340
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:48,240
 And the songs of ascent are probably, you know,

341
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:51,680
 collected and shaped together during the exile

342
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:52,880
 of the people.

343
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:54,920
 And when the people of Israel,

344
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:57,960
 when the Jewish people had no political power

345
00:20:57,960 --> 00:21:00,840
 and they were scattered around the world,

346
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:05,560
 yet even then, the gatherness of worship,

347
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:08,440
 when the people coming together to worship,

348
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:13,440
 the Psalm says, the worship, gathering worship itself

349
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,520
 is a sacred, holy thing.

350
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:20,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

351
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:25,360
 You know, I have been growing up in the church

352
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:34,840
 for decades, for decades.

353
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:36,560
 Oh man, I'm getting old.

354
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:41,400
 And the church is never perfect.

355
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,880
 The church is never perfect.

356
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:46,880
 And sometimes, you know, in my experience of the church,

357
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:49,200
 the church can break my heart.

358
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:53,480
 The church can hurt me and disappoint me.

359
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:57,640
 You know, I must say with a disclaimer,

360
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:59,800
 I must include myself, you know.

361
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:02,040
 I disappoint someone else.

362
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:04,320
 I break someone's heart.

363
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:05,840
 You know, I have to include myself.

364
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:07,680
 The church is not perfect.

365
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:09,640
 But, you know, along the years,

366
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:12,240
 I have never given up on the church.

367
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:14,720
 Never given up on the church.

368
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:17,520
 It's not because the church is perfect.

369
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:20,720
 It's not because church is always a happy place.

370
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:25,720
 But because I understand the church is the very plan of God.

371
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:31,480
 As long as God is God, God's church will remain.

372
00:22:31,480 --> 00:22:36,360
 (speaking in foreign language)

373
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:50,960
 So I understand my identity as the member of the church.

374
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,920
 I have a calling.

375
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:55,400
 And the calling is a sacred calling.

376
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,400
 It is a community Christ purchased

377
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,920
 with His blood and His sacrifice.

378
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,600
 It's not because of me.

379
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:04,040
 It's because of what Christ has done.

380
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:08,320
 And He redeemed a people and called it the church,

381
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,240
 called it His body.

382
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:12,800
 And the church belongs to Christ Jesus.

383
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:16,720
 (speaking in foreign language)

384
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:22,720
 So verse three here, not only the gathering of the people,

385
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:26,400
 the church is sacred.

386
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,400
 Not because we're perfect,

387
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:32,040
 but what God's grace has done and make it sacred.

388
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:33,080
 Verse three, it says,

389
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:37,680
 "It is as if the gathering of people worshiping together,

390
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:42,160
 as if the two of Hermon, Mount Hermon,

391
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:46,440
 were falling on Mount Zion, Jerusalem.

392
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:48,520
 For there the Lord bestows His blessing,

393
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:50,200
 even life forevermore."

394
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:54,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

395
00:23:54,120 --> 00:24:01,720
 Now this is the second image of the Psalm.

396
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:06,080
 No, the first one is the anointing of the high priest Aaron.

397
00:24:06,080 --> 00:24:09,880
 The second images here is a geographical image.

398
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:12,080
 You know, when people are united,

399
00:24:12,080 --> 00:24:17,080
 it is like two of Mount Hermon falling on Mount Zion.

400
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:22,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

401
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:30,960
 Now Mount Hermon is the highest mountain

402
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:32,280
 in the land of Israel.

403
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:35,000
 It is about 9,000 feet tall.

404
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,920
 And it is sometimes called the Snow-Capped Mountain

405
00:24:37,920 --> 00:24:39,280
 or Gray-Haired Mountain.

406
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,760
 You know why?

407
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:45,760
 Because the mountain is so elevated

408
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:49,000
 and it's always capped by snow.

409
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:52,440
 In much of the year, it's a snow-capped mountain.

410
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:57,240
 (speaking in foreign language)

411
00:24:57,240 --> 00:25:02,120
 In the land of Palestine,

412
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:07,120
 from April, around April, May to October,

413
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:10,160
 that is the hot and dry summer.

414
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:13,920
 And there is very little rain, no rain at all.

415
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:17,000
 And everything is dry and the ground,

416
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:20,600
 the soil becomes dry and the crops can die

417
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:22,920
 unless one thing happen.

418
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:26,080
 And that is the morning moisture.

419
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:28,320
 You know, when you wake up very early in the morning,

420
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:30,680
 you look at your yard, right?

421
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:33,840
 There's a layer of moisture.

422
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:37,160
 And because of that, because the mist, the dew,

423
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:40,560
 that bring water to the soil and to sustain us.

424
00:25:40,560 --> 00:25:43,080
 That is life, the dew is life.

425
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:47,920
 (speaking in foreign language)

426
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:58,800
 So in the imagination of the Psalm,

427
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:01,680
 it says when the dew of Mount Hermon,

428
00:26:01,680 --> 00:26:03,760
 the highest mountain, the Snow-Capped Mountain,

429
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:08,760
 comes upon the land and even riches Jerusalem

430
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:12,160
 and Mount Zion, you know, you get the imagery.

431
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:16,720
 It talks about life-giving, refreshment,

432
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:20,120
 you know, fertility and life.

433
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:24,040
 (speaking in foreign language)

434
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:30,680
 So, you know, when we get together,

435
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:33,480
 when the people of God get together,

436
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:37,640
 worship God together, it's kind of like a first taste,

437
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:41,880
 you know, it's like the appetizer

438
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:45,800
 of what heaven is like, what eternal life is like.

439
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:48,200
 You know, when we get together to worship,

440
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:50,680
 to love God together, we will taste

441
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:52,720
 what eternal life is all about.

442
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:56,640
 (speaking in foreign language)

443
00:26:56,640 --> 00:27:02,960
 Now, you remember toward the end of last year,

444
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:05,600
 we had a baptism here, right?

445
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:08,520
 And three people got baptized from our congregation.

446
00:27:08,520 --> 00:27:13,520
 And at baptism, sometimes we recite the Apostles' Creed.

447
00:27:13,520 --> 00:27:17,560
 Remember that, Apostles' Creed?

448
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:20,360
 And Apostles' Creed is a summary of faith

449
00:27:20,360 --> 00:27:23,840
 and the Creed has many different articles

450
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:28,600
 to summarize the most basic elements of Christian faith.

451
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:32,000
 And we call them Apostles' Creed.

452
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:35,840
 And there's a summary and it mentions, as you can tell,

453
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:39,600
 it mentions the church twice.

454
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:42,280
 It says, "I believe the Holy Catholic Church

455
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:45,600
 "and I believe the chameleon of saints."

456
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:49,520
 (speaking in foreign language)

457
00:27:49,520 --> 00:28:01,600
 See, the article says, "I believe in Catholic Church."

458
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:06,600
 Most of the modern people, when we heard the word Catholic,

459
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:11,600
 we immediately think of the Roman Catholic Church, right?

460
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:12,920
 Catholicism.

461
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:16,200
 No, that's not what Apostles' Creed means.

462
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:18,720
 It says Catholic because the word Catholic

463
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:23,720
 actually means universal, worldwide church.

464
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:29,040
 And I believe God's will is to set up the Catholic Church,

465
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:31,600
 which is universal church.

466
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:35,520
 (speaking in foreign language)

467
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:44,520
 See, we, as Christians, we profess the name of Jesus.

468
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:47,280
 We belong to that Catholic Church,

469
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:51,160
 that one worldwide church.

470
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:52,800
 And also, another article, it says,

471
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:55,320
 "The chameleon of saints that I believe."

472
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:56,760
 Now, what does it mean?

473
00:28:56,760 --> 00:28:57,600
 What does it mean?

474
00:28:57,600 --> 00:29:00,760
 It means all Christians, chameleon,

475
00:29:00,760 --> 00:29:03,720
 we share something together.

476
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:05,400
 We're united to Christ,

477
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:09,120
 and therefore we are connected somehow with each other.

478
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,960
 It's like you, you know,

479
00:29:10,960 --> 00:29:13,460
 how many of you like going hiking?

480
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:16,320
 How many of you?

481
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:17,800
 No?

482
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:18,640
 Oh my God.

483
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:20,760
 Okay, all right, only a few.

484
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:24,800
 It's like you go on hiking, on a hiking trail, you know,

485
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:27,840
 and then you go from your starting point,

486
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:30,320
 and then you have a destination to go to, right?

487
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:32,800
 And then along the trail, along the path,

488
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:36,680
 and then you meet some people on the way, right?

489
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:38,560
 Maybe you'll meet some people

490
00:29:38,560 --> 00:29:40,920
 going in a different direction, you know?

491
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:44,920
 They eventually will go to a different destination.

492
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:47,280
 Now, you don't have much to share with them.

493
00:29:47,280 --> 00:29:50,040
 However, if you, on the trip,

494
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:55,040
 you meet some people going to the same destination,

495
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:57,120
 and then that was the moment you go,

496
00:29:57,120 --> 00:30:00,440
 aha, you know, I'm going to that destination,

497
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:02,920
 and you are going to that destination too.

498
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:05,800
 And that's why we are on the way together.

499
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:09,440
 When you meet some people going to the same destination,

500
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:10,280
 you find that, okay,

501
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:13,880
 you have so much more to share with them.

502
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:17,800
 (speaking in foreign language)

503
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:21,720
 (speaking in foreign language)

504
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:37,200
 So it says, we believe the chameleon,

505
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:40,440
 the connectedness, togetherness of saints.

506
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:44,080
 Now, the word saints means all Christians.

507
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:47,120
 It does not mean that we are holy.

508
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:50,360
 We're not holy, we're not perfect, right?

509
00:30:50,360 --> 00:30:53,320
 But we are saints somehow in Christ

510
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:56,240
 because Christ made us holy and righteous,

511
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:57,880
 all because Christ has done.

512
00:30:57,880 --> 00:31:00,120
 So chameleon means we have shared life.

513
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:03,520
 Chameleon means we have fellowship,

514
00:31:03,520 --> 00:31:07,480
 and we share one faith, we share one worship,

515
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:09,680
 and we share one salvation.

516
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:13,600
 (speaking in foreign language)

517
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:18,520
 (speaking in foreign language)

518
00:31:18,520 --> 00:31:28,200
 And together we take this psalm,

519
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:31,000
 and I have some applications for us.

520
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:34,560
 I think the first application from Psalm 133 is,

521
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:38,880
 thank God for other Christians,

522
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:41,280
 for other brothers and sisters, right?

523
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:43,280
 I would say to God, dear God, thank you

524
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:47,680
 that I am not alone, I'm not alone hiking.

525
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:51,400
 I'm with other people.

526
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:54,560
 Thank God for brother and sister who pray for me,

527
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:57,920
 who are being with me, who are walking alongside me,

